<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17501205-64">
               <interp inst="t17501205-64" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17501205-64" type="year" value="1750"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17501205-64" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17501205"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17501205-64" type="date" value="17501205"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17501205-64-off324-c406" targOrder="Y" targets="t17501205-64-defend538 t17501205-64-off324 t17501205-64-verdict328"></join>
         
               <p>80. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17501205-64-defend538" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Hardwick 
                  <interp inst="t17501205-64-defend538" type="surname" value="Hardwick"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-defend538" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-defend538" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17501205-64-off324" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-off324" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-off324" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a brass hilted hanger, value 4 s.
            </rs> the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17501205-64-victim540" type="victimName">
                     James 
                     Palace 
                  <interp inst="t17501205-64-victim540" type="surname" value="Palace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-victim540" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-victim540" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17501205-64-off324 t17501205-64-victim540"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17501205-64-cd325" type="crimeDate">Nov. 16</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17501205-64-off324 t17501205-64-cd325"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17501205-64-person541">
                  James 
                  Palace 
               <interp inst="t17501205-64-person541" type="surname" value="Palace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-person541" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-person541" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in <placeName id="t17501205-64-crimeloc326">the Minories</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17501205-64-crimeloc326" type="placeName" value="the Minories"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17501205-64-crimeloc326" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17501205-64-off324 t17501205-64-crimeloc326"></join> and <rs id="t17501205-64-viclabel327" type="occupation">keep a sale shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17501205-64-victim540 t17501205-64-viclabel327"></join>, on Friday the 16th of Nov. about 3 in the afternoon Mr. Steed called out; 
               <persName id="t17501205-64-person542">
                  Ann 
                  White 
               <interp inst="t17501205-64-person542" type="surname" value="White"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-person542" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-person542" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who looks after the shop, asked what was the matter; he made answer, had not you a hanger in the window? she answered, yes sir, and it is in the window still. I believe, said he, a man has run away with it: upon which I run out, and Mr. Steed and several others went in pursuit. I overtook the prisoner in Rosemary-branch Alley, I took him by the collar and asked him where the hanger was. I saw it in his bosom and took it out, produced in court and deposed to.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17501205-64-person543">
                  William 
                  Steed 
               <interp inst="t17501205-64-person543" type="surname" value="Steed"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-person543" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-person543" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , on the 16th of Nov. about 3 in the afternoon, I met the prisoner at the bar, near the prosecutor's shop, and two other men with him.<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175012050032"></xptr> The prisoner stopped and look'd into the shop, I was about 6 yards off at that time, I saw him take a hanger out of the window and turned at the corner, and there husled it under his coat: he walked along till he overtook one of his companions, then I run to the prosecutor's shop, and call'd, &amp;c. We went after him and took the prisoner with the hanger upon him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17501205-64-verdict328" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-verdict328" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17501205-64-punish329" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17501205-64-punish329" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17501205-64-defend538 t17501205-64-punish329"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
